    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="852"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12762.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith translated
                    copies of a communication received from Senor Isidro Fabela, Acting Secretary of
                    Foreign Relations for General Carranza, First Chief of the Constitutionalist
                    Army, relative to my communication sent General Carranza as to the instruction
                    from the Department<note n="55" xml:id="d852fn55">Telegram of July 27.</note>
                    relative to the naming by Francisco Carbajal of General Lauro Villar and David
                    Gutierrez Allende as his representatives to treat with General Carranza.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John R. Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head"
                        >[Untitled]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-28">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>By instructions of the First Chief of the Constitutionalist Army, I beg to
                        thank you for the information which his excellency Secretary Bryan has given
                        him through you, regarding the naming by Licenciado Francisco Carbajal of
                        General Lauro Villar and David Gutierrez Allende as his representatives to
                        treat with Mr. Carranza regarding the unconditional surrender of the
                        ex-federal army and the powers he received from General Huerta.</p>
                    <p>At the same time I take pleasure in advising you that Mr. Carranza has given
                        orders to General Pablo Gonzalez, Chief of the Army Corps of the Northeast,
                        to protect and facilitate their trip to Saltillo. I also should tell you
                        that the same orders have been repeated to San Luis Potosi, giving the names
                        of the delegates and instructing the Saltillo authorities to protect and
                        respect them.</p>
                    <p>I appreciate your good will in furnishing this information and am pleased to
                        reiterate [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Isidro Fabela</hi>
                        </signed>.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
